  "for_tenant": "dna:tenant:6XBZ93FSHN5TRX8MCS5R66FNCM",
  "_about": "The three canonical lifecycle Step definitions a LifecycleRun points at when it records a unit of work being opened or shipped. Each is a reusable recipe (a prov:Plan, per ADR-001): the run is the activity that happened, the Step is the named kind of work it carried out. change-started marks a sulis-change start completing; change-shipped marks a sulis-change mark-shipped completing; unclassified-lifecycle-step is the catch-all when a run names a step we don't yet recognise. The run links to its Step via the sulis:viaStep relation. These three ULIDs are authored here once and copied — never re-minted — by the runs and the migration that reference them, so they stay byte-stable. mechanism is mixed because each lifecycle moment is part automated command, part human or agent decision. for_process=lifecycle and the tenant ULID are byte-identical to the canonical identifiers pinned in the requirements document and shared across every reference. The founder-readable note lives here at the envelope, not per-Step, because the foundation Step schema (v1.2.0) sets unevaluatedProperties:false and rejects a per-Step note field — the same pattern the release-train and discover-project Step sets follow.",
  "captured_on": "2026-06-03",

